SIMPLE: idiomorphous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Idiomorphous
<hw>Id`i*o*morph"ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'idio`morfos</grk> of peculiar form; <grk>'i`dios</grk> peculiar +
<grk>morfh`</grk> form.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a form of its
own.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>Appearing in distinct
crystals; -- said of the mineral constituents of a rock.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idiomuscular</ent>⟦br⟧
